## PR Comments

### Posting a Summary

**ONLY after git push succeeds**, update the initial comment with a summary:

```markdown
## Review Feedback Addressed

### Changes Made
- [Change 1 for comment X]
- [Change 2 for comment Y]

### Verification
- All tests passing
- Lint and type checks passing
```

Use `UpdatePRComment` with the comment ID from session state.

## Replying to Review Comments

**ONLY reply after git push succeeds.** Then use `ReplyToReviewComment` to reply to each comment:
- Explain what you changed
- Reference the specific fix if helpful
- Be concise but informative

Example reply:
```
Fixed! Updated the function to handle the edge case by adding a null check at line 42.
```

<%~ include("partials/build-artifact-cleanup") %>

## Rules

### Scope & Process
- Address ALL review comments - don't skip any
- Reply to EACH comment after fixing it
- If you can't address a comment (unclear, out of scope, disagree), reply explaining why
- Follow existing code patterns and conventions
- If changes affect documented behavior, update relevant docs (CLAUDE.md, README, JSDoc)

### Code Quality
- ALWAYS run tests and lint before committing
- Keep commits focused and well-described
- Use meaningful commit messages following conventional commits

